    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d9906fa3_75e084ae",
        "filename": "include/core/SkPostConfig.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 136,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-28T13:22:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this is all fine as-is.  Would it be clearer if we used __attribute__((noreturn)) / __declspec(noreturn) on sk_abort_no_print()?  That\u0027s the focused version of SkUNREACHABLE, telling the compiler that the function returning is undefined behavior no matter where it\u0027s called.",
      "parentUuid": "fad38c8d_6b4cee32",
      "revId": "74c19de3beda545f5809e6305e02057e5329e340",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e36e4115_e3a6af5c",
        "filename": "include/core/SkPostConfig.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 136,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-28T13:48:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we put SkUNREACHABLE here so that we could remove returns like this: \n\n  SkColorType foo() {\n    //...\n    SK_ABORT(\"unexpected something or other\");\n    return kUnknown_SkColorType;\n  }\n\nIIRC before this GCC would warn if we removed that return. If tagging sk_abort_no_print() as noreturn squashes the warning then removing SkUNREACHABLE here seems fine.",
      "parentUuid": "d9906fa3_75e084ae",
      "revId": "74c19de3beda545f5809e6305e02057e5329e340",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4518ae07_2021f561",
        "filename": "include/core/SkPostConfig.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 136,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-28T13:50:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, tagging a function as noreturn essentially puts an SkUNREACHABLE after every call site.\n\nI think what we\u0027ve got here is fine.",
      "parentUuid": "e36e4115_e3a6af5c",
      "revId": "74c19de3beda545f5809e6305e02057e5329e340",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6c8d0f14_bca0f0cc",
        "filename": "include/core/SkPostConfig.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 136,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-28T14:24:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "sk_abort_no_print is currently not declared [[noreturn]], so the compiler can still elide all of this and I don\u0027t think it\u0027s fine. I think we should just tag sk_abort_no_print with [[noreturn]] and remove the use of \u0027unreachable\u0027.",
      "parentUuid": "4518ae07_2021f561",
      "revId": "74c19de3beda545f5809e6305e02057e5329e340",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
